

to add a new rule:


sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=3389/tcp
then reload the firewall service:

sudo firewall-cmd --reload



you must indicate the protocol 'tcp' or 'udp'

to remove :

sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --remove-port=22/tcp


remember that there are zones that you can use with --zone=public inside the command 
___
with ufw just run:

sudo ufw allow 3389


